name: invalid_utf8_lone_high_surrogate
description: |
  This is the three-byte sequence ED A0 80, the direct UTF-8 encoding that a
  permissive encoder might emit for the lone high surrogate U+D800. Surrogate
  code points are not Unicode scalar values and are excluded from well-formed
  UTF-8, so a conforming encoder must fail rather than produce these bytes.

  This fixture corresponds to a string value such as `"\\ud800"` in runtimes
  that permit unpaired UTF-16 surrogates in their string representation.

  See the Unicode definition of well-formed UTF-8 (D92 and Table 3-7):
  https://www.unicode.org/versions/Unicode15.0.0/ch03.pdf
format: hex
decode-as: bytes
invalid-as: utf8
tags:
  - "encoding"
  - "unicode"
  - "utf8"
  - "invalid-utf8"
  - "surrogate"
  - "lone-surrogate"
  - "high-surrogate"
---
ed a0 80   # Invalid direct UTF-8 encoding of U+D800
